  "text": "TJQ is a two-lane tunnel located in the center of São Paulo and characterized mainly by LDV traffic. The direction of the traffic in this tunnel alternated twice a day at 06:00 and 09:00. TJQ has a length of 1.9 km, a speed limit of 60 km h −1 , and a natural wind flow velocity ranging from 1.0 to 4.9 m s −1 during congested and normal traffic conditions, respectively [CITATION_1] . TRA is located on the outskirts of the city on a highway ring. This tunnel is an important alternative route for HDVs due to traffic restrictions in the center of São Paulo. With a length of 1.7 km and a speed limit of 70 km h −1 , the traffic flow is always on four lanes in one direction. [CITATION_2] described that the natural flow velocity ranged from 1.0 to 6.1 m s −1 during congested and normal traffic conditions, respectively.",
